$V_{26, 6} = 2056 + 26 = 2082$.
$M_{26} = 2082 + 26 - 1 = 2107$.

The number $N=2026$ is between $V_{26, 3} = 2004$ and $V_{26, 4} = 2030$.
$2004 < 2026 < 2030$.
This means $N$ is in the segment between $V_{26, 3}$ and $V_{26, 4}$. The length of this segment is 26.
The position of $N$ in this segment (starting from $V_{26, 3}$ as position 1) is:
$p = 2026 - 2004 = 22$.
So, $N$ is the 22nd number in the segment of length 26.

For a number $N$ in the interior of a segment of length $k$, the three pairs of opposite neighbors have differences $2k, 2k, 2k$.
